snippet: Katinka Hosszu of Hungary broke two world records at the short-course world championships in Doha, Qatar, in the women’s 200-meter backstroke and 100 individual medley.
lead_paragraph: Katinka Hosszu of Hungary broke two world records at the short-course world championships in Doha, Qatar, in the women’s 200-meter backstroke and 100 individual medley.

headline.main: Hungarian Sets Two Women’s Marks at Swimming Championships
